<paragraph id="007606418ED3FF5D48A752CBFEBDFA0F" blockId="157.[151,1436,151,2035]" box="[151,280,1511,1535]" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ED3FF5D489052CBFEAAFA0F" box="[160,271,1511,1535]" captionStart="PLATE 41" captionStartId="159.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[261,1330,223,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-94@159.[241,1345,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 41. A, C, E. Chelae. B, D. Male genitalia. A. Anteon punctum, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). B. A. qinlingense, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). C. A. quatei from Malaya (from Olmi 1998e). D. Anteon quatei, paratype (from Olmi 1991). E. A. raptor, holotype (from Olmi 1998e). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.23 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278512/files/figure.png" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Plate 41A</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED3FF5D48A7511CFD75F9B6" blockId="157.[151,1436,151,2035]" box="[151,720,1584,1606]" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Anteon punctum Xu, He &amp; Olmi in He &amp; Xu 2002: 191.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED3FF5E48A7515EFE52FECF" blockId="157.[151,1436,151,2035]" lastBlockId="158.[151,1436,151,2034]" lastPageId="158" lastPageNumber="159" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
Description of Female. Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48ED3FF5D4AAE515EFD53F97A" box="[670,758,1650,1674]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible, clypeus and anterior fourth of face testaceous; antenna brown, except segments 1 and 10 testaceous; mesosoma black, except posterior margin of pronotum testaceous; metasoma brown; legs testaceous. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 11.5:7:12:10.5:10.5:9:8.5:8:8:11. Head shiny, smooth, punctate, unsculptured among punctures; frontal line complete; POL = 3.5; OL = 3; OOL = 5.5; OPL = 4.5; TL = 6; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli as long as OL; occipital carina complete. Pronotum with anterior surface dull, transversely striate; posterior surface shiny, strongly punctate, unsculptured among punctures, slightly shorter than scutum (11.5:15.5), approximately as broad as long (11.5:12); pronotal tubercle reaching tegula. Scutum shiny, smooth, punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.8–0.9 length of scutum. Scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Propodeum with strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; dorsal surface reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels and median area as rugose as lateral areas. Fore wing hyaline, slightly yellowish; distal part of stigmal vein much shorter than proximal part (5.5:13). Protarsal segments in following proportions: 22:8:13:46:81. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ED0FF5E489057F3FEAAFF07" box="[160,271,223,247]" captionStart="PLATE 41" captionStartId="159.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[261,1330,223,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-94@159.[241,1345,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 41. A, C, E. Chelae. B, D. Male genitalia. A. Anteon punctum, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). B. A. qinlingense, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). C. A. quatei from Malaya (from Olmi 1998e). D. Anteon quatei, paratype (from Olmi 1991). E. A. raptor, holotype (from Olmi 1998e). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.23 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278512/files/figure.png" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Plate 41A</figureCitation>
) with proximal prominence bearing one long bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ED0FF5E4C4857F3FB42FF07" box="[1144,1255,223,247]" captionStart="PLATE 41" captionStartId="159.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[261,1330,223,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-94@159.[241,1345,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 41. A, C, E. Chelae. B, D. Male genitalia. A. Anteon punctum, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). B. A. qinlingense, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). C. A. quatei from Malaya (from Olmi 1998e). D. Anteon quatei, paratype (from Olmi 1991). E. A. raptor, holotype (from Olmi 1998e). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.23 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278512/files/figure.png" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Plate 41A</figureCitation>
) with basal part shorter than distal part (21:60), with two rows of 37 (28 + 10) lamellae and 34 (17 + 17) bristles; distal apex with six lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED0FF5E48F75660FE2BFE94" blockId="158.[151,1436,151,2034]" box="[199,398,332,356]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
